        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 13 at 4:29PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 429 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Salem, moving north at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Roanoke...
Salem...
Troutville...
New Castle...
Catawba...
Fincastle...
and Nace.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
